        <briefdescription>
<para>This function retrieves an immediately connected RX device&apos;s Extended Display Identification Data (EDID) structure. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_dp_psu" kindref="compound">XDpPsu</ref> instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Edid</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the Edid buffer to save to.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if the I2C transactions to read the EDID were successful.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_ERROR_COUNT_MAX if the EDID read request timed out.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_DEVICE_NOT_FOUND if no RX device is connected.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE otherwise.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
